content: Downloaded the app after a friend sent me a link to a trail we're considering. Perhaps I am doing something wrong in the app navigation, but once I choose a trail from the trail list I cannot figure out how to get back to the list. I like to find new trails and review options before heading out for the day. I have to close and reopen after I read about every trail. Really annoying. Also, the search feature doesn't have the ability to sort by distance, difficulty, etc. Pointless. Deleting.

This app could be SO much better. Unlike on the website, there is no ability to filter trails. In addition, there is no "legend" so you are left to decide if something is a hiking trail or a ski run. There is no ability to select trail segments & add them together to construct a different route with ascent/descent/length, etc. I like how snappy the map painting is. I'm hard pressed to think what else I like. I'm hoping this improves A LOT before I need it. For now, I've got multiple apps.

This app is good because it has features such as offline maps that are usually found only in the premium version of other similar apps. But it lacks a few features that will make it much better. First, the search function is very poor. It is difficult to gwt what you are looking for, and some trails seem to be entirely missing from this app. Second, the app forces you to download a region offline before you can do anything. Also should implement directions to trailheads.
replyContent: Hi Balaji, thanks for your feedback.  We're working on improving search over the next few weeks!  Also, directions are available on the trail screen with the Driving Directions button.  Our app is a community resource with data contributed by users.  We encourage everyone to upload tracks, descriptions, and photos at https://www.hikingproject.com.

content: (1) I can't review saved hikes. In particular, the map overlay of my route is unavailable on review. What's the point of saving it if I can't review where I was? (2) The app lacks internal consistency for distance hiked. I hiked a path for the first and only time and it was recorded as 7.9 miles in one part of the app and 8.2 miles in another. This is for the ONE AND ONLY journey I made on this route, so it's not possible to be reporting for two different journeys with different distances. (3) Wayfinding is made easier real-time when I think I have lost the trail. It has been helpful for this.

I really like the web version but the Android app has a long way to go. When I search for a particular trail that is highlighted and recommended on the web version, it shows in the results but not on the navigation map. In fact many trails are not showing up on the map. Western North Carolina looks like it has nothing to hike. Unless I am using the app incorrectly, this version is unusable at this time for my location

This has been the best hiking app I can find. But sometimes I can't always find the trails I am looking for on this app, and I have to use a different app. Some of these trail reviews are stupid. "There were mosquitos," "it was muddy." Well, you are outside..duh. Also, it would be nice to have a feature where I can create my own route, especially where many trail systems converge.

This app is great! My only complaint is regarding the photo carousel. Its extremely annoying to look through photos of various trails because the carousel is on a timer, but when I try to manually flip through photos the carousel timer goes off and flips to the next photo. It happens very often and I sometimes spend 5 or more seconds trying to land on the correct photo. Hence, the 3 star rating.

Great app. Is only really missing one big thing that I think would perfect it. They need to add the function/ability to plan ahead on your hike! There's a ton of trails that join others and continue on that I would love to be able to plan a trip on but the app doesn't make me able to do that. Would be very nice to be able to trace out a map/trail of where I plan to or would like to hike.

I love that I don't have to download an area before going, that it works offline. I wish it had more trails, especially ones that are well marked and noted at the trailhead. My FAV hiking app! And love that I can see where I am on the map, and if I got off trail. And the altitude mapping (peaks and valleys) is very handy, especially figuring out how difficult a trail is

It does not properly download the maps. So if you're going to use it, make sure you zoom in on the entire area you're going to be in, with both topo and sat maps *while you still have internet* so they're cached. This is unacceptable since it claims to have downloaded the maps. Also if you accidentally hit finish on a hike recording, you can't back out and continue recording. So the UI needs some work too.

The app looks nice, but I found it hard to navigate. More importantly, it is missing the most important feature any hiking/backpacking app absolutely NEEDS: the ability to filter trails based on location, length, difficulty, type, etc. Without filtering, this app is useless to me as a backpacker. There are way too many trails to rummage through manually without knowing if I can backpack on them.

I hate the new update. I loved this app because I could get accurate information about the inclines at any point of the hike. Now it's super jumpy and not user friendly at all. The range of what the color red represents is way to large. Please bring back the option to pick precise locations on a trail to see the incline or add new colors for steep inclines. Having red represent anything over 15% makes it hard to tell what im really in for, a 50% incline is extremely harder than 15%.

Great idea, but needs more work. My biggest complaint: when recording it constantly zooms back out so that the WHOLE recording is on screen even when I've zoomed in so I can see the detail of the area where I am at the moment. Also sometimes it pegs my location miles away (I think possibly from a cell tower ping) and I can't find a way to edit or remove the point from the recording.

Just downloaded the app and so far its easy to use, good UI, and high quality content. Immediate "issue" that I think would skyrocket this app into a 5 or 6 star rating is a filter option when searching for trails. Being able to filter distance, altitude change, difficulty, and even star ratings by users would be such a quick and easy way to significantly improve the app.

How does this app average such a high score? The back button has random behavior and you can't use it to exit the app at all. Each trail may or may not have all the listing elements (elevation, etc) - not even placeholders. Driving directions sometimes take you to the end of the trail instead of the trailhead. And the last trail I hiked is permanently pinned to every page I go to.

The Hiking Project changed the way I hike. It's extremely straightforward, uncluttered and intuitive unlike other hiking apps I've tried. When you open the app a topographical map pops up with your current location in conjunction with the trails around unlike other apps that bloat the screen with a description of the trail and what others think about it before displaying it's location in a remotely understandable fashion. I love this app. Thank you to the developers and crowdfunders.

Really cool app. My favorite feature is that you can download the trail map and still use it offline while still being located on the map with real ACCURACY. I reccomend this for avid hikers and even people just going for a walk in the woods. I've used this in Yellowstone as well as back in Indiana for those parks that don't always have the best paper maps available.

Offline maps work, records where you've been, keeps a log of recorded hikes. Web app is easier to use, on phone or PC. Favorites list helps remember hikes to do again. No route planning using multiple trails. Needs some bug fixes, new features, but apparently no longer being actively maintained.

Recently hiked a 7.5 mile loop in the Ozark National Forest along the Buffalo River in Arkansas. Did a trail with about a 1400 ft elevation change and made several river crossings. This app, on airplane mode and no wifi, kept us on the trail using our gps location. Many trail junctions were overgrown and undetectable with the human eye but the app kept us on trail regardless. For a free app, this think was awesome! Saved us hours of backtracking and the possibility of getting lost.

I am an avid hiker, & what seemed like a very promising app just would not work. You cannot check into a trail without signing up or logging in, & I can't do either because of a constant message about rough weather due to their servers being 'temporarily' down (this occurring over a period of several days). A shame, as I heard great things about this app & was really looking forward to using it. Uninstalling & moving on.
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback on Hiking Project.  We didn't have any scheduled downtime or other reported issues during that timeframe, and the logs look normal, but we'll watch for more info.  FYI, you don't need an account for most of the features, such as viewing maps, trails, photos, conditions, or comments.

content: This app has so much potential and in some ways breasts most other apps for features, but the trail maps are terrible for my state anyway. At least 50 percent of the trails are missing, even the national Forest trails for much of the state are missing. Even national trails are missing. It would also be nice if they added land ownership like Trailforks. The only reason I give the app 3 stars is it generally works with showing topography on maps when you are offline when many apps will not.

It's a good app, but I miss the feature where we used to be able to add trails to a to-do list. Also it would be super helpful if there could be a comment section for details on conditions and other stuff like there is on Mountain project. Also seems to be missing some trails compared to AllTrails (e.g.)

Needs improvement. Cannot add photos or review trails in app. Only post conditions. Also missing many significant trail systems. For example, Wayne National Forest has no trails listed in this app. I realize this is all user input but it would be nice if you could track and add trail routes such as in the AllTrails app. Hiking Project is the easiest app to use though and I utilized it when hiking in Colorado in addition to other apps and maps. Same for the REI bike trail app. Missing huge trails

Good resource for trails, but several flaws that make it much less useful than it could be. If not recording a hike, you can follow position along a known trail quite accurately When recording a hike the ability to see where you are disappears... VERY INCONVENIENT. App also seems to rely on cell tower triangulation for positioning. When the app loses a cell tower, it loses position and then goes haywire. It has 'tracked" 11-12 miles on several recentt 3 mi hikes.

Screen navigation terrible - first time I use it maps don't look too bad even though descriptions aren't so great, so I choose a trail - and there's no way to get back to the main list of trails. Go to the help page (web link) and there's even an FAQ asking how do I get back to the main list of trails. Not a good sign. It says click the icon in the upper left - but there is no icon on the upper left! Using Android on Samsung Galaxy 8 plus.

This is my navigation app of choice when I'm out backpacking (to supplement paper maps of course). The trails included are very comprehensive, though many remote or unmarked trails are not mapped here. I sometimes have problems moving the map around/zooming, and scrolling along the elevation profile feature is a bit buggy, but otherwise this is pretty great.

I started using the app July 2020. Once I figured it out, it did well tracking/recording my hikes. Since December 2020 it has performed horribly. Zero accuracy. I tried uninstalling and reinstalling. No improvement. I have waited beyond the 2 week Friday updates. No change to correct tracked routes. Cannot rely on this app for recording tracks to refer to at a later date. Wish I could add a photo of my last 'wild' tracks. Would explain well what I am trying to describe.

I do love this app, and the MTN bike project one as well!! Super simple, but has pretty much all the trails I use, which is all I need. The only thing I would really like to have as an option, is for users to submit campsite locations. I have a trail in GA that I like to overnight backpack, but using these maps, I have no idea where all the campsites are.

Maps are easily downloaded for offline viewing. It's cool to see your progress mapped on both the map and the elevation graph. I wish there was more customization in defining a trail before you actually record it - I'd like to define a trail on the map and then go hike it.

I want to really like this app, but unless I'm missing something, to check in to a hike you have to finish the hike then report the distance hiked. In an area with multiple intersecting trails, if I make my own loop out of 4 of them I have no way of recording this or checking in because my milage will be way different from the trail I started at. It's too bad you can't "start" a hike and have it follow your hike and at the end record your hike. It should use GPS to track distance automatically.

This app is really nice. It has a nice listing of trails with information and photos. The trail info can be downloaded and used offline which is important since trails tend to be in the middle of the woods with no reception. Finding trails in the local area is easy. I can bring up the map and list all the short hikes nearby. This app will be staying on my phone.

Offline hiking maps, GPS, free; excellent! I installed this app after realizing the "free" version of a popular hiking app would be completely unusable for my weeklong hiking trip in the North Cascades. Hiking Project was essential for planning hikes and checking out elevations and trail steepness.

The interface is really great and there are lots of trails, even some that don't show up on all trails. The recording function does use a lot of power, and I would like to see a better way to tell how much of the distance and elevation I have hiked and are left.

Doesn't work offline. Like, it's about going on trails where there may be no cell coverage, but despite downloading areas ahead of time, the app doesn't know where I am on the planet. Why doesn't gps location work? So useless.

Doesn't properly record hikes, keeps recording me several miles from where I started randomly throughout the hike. Can't display the map of the trail I want to be following while using record....that's the entire point of these type of apps. Much of the trail info in Montana is not correct, but no way to contribute on the app. Pretty disappointed, but two stars because it has more trails mapped in Montana than AllTrails.

Excellent app - great "live navigation" function which allows hiker to continuously check progress on the trail, and if you're still on the trail...the app has saved me a few times when I lost my way at a trail junction. Wish they could incorporate it into a smart watch!

some of the clickology just isnt intuitive. for instance i was trying to favorite certain hikes and it talked about pinning them. so i pinned them and it didnt add the hikes to the favorites (to dos). kind of minor since i figured it out but it seems odd in this day and age to have to figure this out. all that being said, ive enjoyed using this app because its definately helped me find the next place to go in one convienent location. i will continue to use this app!

Wanted to love this app, but when I got to the trail head and launched it, the app needed internet access. Really??? Who backpacks where there's even a phone signal, let alone internet access??? Huge fail!!! Might be a setting or something, but I would expert any such app to default to offline use. Fortunately I also had US Topo Maps loaded on my phone, as well as my trusty Garmin 30x.

One of the most useful hiking apps I've found, and completely free with no ads! Hats off. 4 stars because while it's an excellent app, it doesn't have all the trails or off-line map downloading (although it does allow you to download and search for trails offline)

refuses to move data or app onto the sdcard. this renders the app unusable. 3 years later, this is still true. I now have to delete the app because I need another app that has higher priority. Just putting map data on the SD card should be simple and would go a long ways in making this a good app.

Great app. Lots of good information about the trails, and I like the fact that you don't need cell signal to use it on the trail. I do wish you could upload photos and add comments to trails from the app, though.

This is my favorite hiking app, but a recent update has left the menu is inaccessible (3 bars at the top left are gone), hiding the app's best features such as the "gems" list and filters. Without this, you might as well use Alltrails (a far inferior app). If this issue gets resolved I will update my review to 5 stars.

The ad says "everything you need, nothing you don't". That is a lie! It asks you to sign in/create an account to start recording a track. Nobody needs that. Save my track on the device. That needs no account. Make it possible to share or export it. Even that should not require an account but might use one to make some things easier, sure. Uninstalled!

Great app - I was looking for nearby trails since walking through town was no challenge. Found a nearby park that had many & I had no clue they were there. I really enjoy being able to download the maps to my phone and just use gps for finding my way and making sure I'm on the correct path. Highly recommend this app - using Galaxy Note 9

Generously free and rich of features. This app is completely free and offers lot of features for hikers. It doesn't have the library as all trails but it's free and let you do everything for free. Help buy adding trails and hikes to make it rich. You can zoom out the map and see trails near you.

Using this app has been a fantastic experience thus far; it's got a lot of detailed information. I do wish there were a way to view the altitude lines when its zoomed in further. It disappaears at a certain point of zoom currently.

I don't know what radios this app uses but it was pivotal for me on my last trip the George Washington National Forest! Although I had no Cellular signal and my phone was on Airplane mode ( so save battery) I was still able to navigate my difficult trail to safety (we had an emergency). I'd give it a 5 start however there is still room for improvement.

I used this app on the trail yesterday for the first time. I really want to like this app but it has several shortcomings (either it doesn't provide these things or provides them but they are so hidden and/or so undocumented that I could never figure out how to do it): (1) no way to create a route out of existing trails. There is a loop I like to do but in the app this loop is 3 separate trails. No way I could see to join them into a loop so as to get stats (e.g. total distance of the loop) (2) even on a given single trail in the app, the best it seemed to do is show me the blue dot for where I was. That's quasi-useful but what I really wish it would show is things like how far to the destination? How far have I come so far? What elevation gain/loss has happened so far, or how much on the trail ahead?. Somewhat disappointed.

I've tried signing up both through the app and through a desktop. It won't let me complete sign up, even though I met the password requirements, etc. Regardless of search terms, this is not addressed in the Help Center and there is no contact listed for customer service.

The app has an awful, unintuitive UI. It's very difficult to click a trail and bring up the associated page as clicking the trail doesn't take you there. I find it is easier to Google the trail, then click the Google link to get the info.

App is missing the ability to download gpx files. Have to navigate to the website for that feature. Makes the app almost useless since I'm on the website already I just use that. Only real benefit to the app you can find trails offline if you have that state downloaded. But again, if I can't then get the gpx it doesn't do me much good.

The more I use this app the more I find it severally Iacking. Many peaks aren't even listed and tons of popular trails aren't in it. The process to add trails or peaks is clunky and difficult. They need to seriously step their game up, in the meantime I just can't find a good use for this.

It's infuriating. I get stuck in some loop where there's a menu with two options, explore map or download other places. No matter what I click, the stupid menu doesn't go away so I can't even see the map. Downloaded, have it a shot then deleted.

Downloaded the app, found it really hard to use, couldn't scope to the area I'd just selected in search, then once you tap a hike you can't get back to a 'home' to start again. Uninstalled after 15 mins of playing with it, perhaps it's better with some effort but I want willing to try.

I used to enjoy this app. (Updated 4 star to 2). Recent Android 11 changes to location means the record funct of this app no longer works. The developer should use background location and not location. No one stares at their phone the whole time they are hiking. As soon as the screen closes or locks the tracking stops.

love this app! we have been able to find lots of hiking gems using this app. the descriptions are on point and mostly the distances are correct...occasionally they will be off by a half mile to a mile but they probably go by what the park service tells them the distance is. anyway it is very helpful and keeps you on track so you don't get lost:-)

So disappointing. I used to use this application anywhere I went. Updated my phone and now, even though I'm in my account, I can't see my pinned hikes. I can't get the introductory screen to disappear and I can't use the maps to find trails. Completely worthless!

Love the app's look and the fact that it's crowd sourced means the onus is on the community. I've found some gems on here I couldn't find easily elsewhere and the offline modes are very helpful. Only big problem is that for the last couple of months, the back button just doesn't work in this app only. Everything else works great!

Probably should get 4.5 🌟 because many trails are still not listed. All other aspects are great. Good tracking even in areas with poor GPS sign, although on rare occasions it loses signal. Very rare, but it happens. I like trail descriptions, topography, info on ascent, descent, degree of decline, length of trails, and info from others concerning specific trails. I have recommended it to my friends without hesitation.

Wanted to like it and use it. Unfortunately it auto downloaded a state map as soon as I opened it, which I didn't want. Then I went to search a trail in another state. Found the trail, zoomed me to where the general location of the trail is...no trail visible on map, and no trail profile. Guess I'll go back to just using the website, or AllTrails.

Unlike Alltrails, this has freely downloadable maps (though you still need internet to see the trail highlighted). You'll find fewer trails here compared to Alltrails, but the trails here are curated. Hence, start with this app. Then, go to Alltrails if you want something easier or closer.

Awesome app for finding hikes and routes. A note on the new update: please, please get rid of the ting picture to the left of the elevation/mile tracker map. The picture crowds out the most important part of this app! And besides it's too small to see anyway.

Great for a free app. Would benefit from being able to mark locations of campsites, trailhead, parking, water sources, hazards, or great views. And pin planned stops. Otherwise great for a map with gps location and some trails mapped out.

This app did work great in recording hikes. Last two uses tracked points only and showed straight line connection. No longer accurate. What is the fix? Update. No longer shows location. Phone GPS is working but the app does not respond. Guess the December 8 update did.more harm than good.

This app is great but some trails start middle of mountain. i want to know the distance from a trail head to there. Ant this is really annoying feature of picture auto slide. I can't stop a picture what I want. please disable auto slide mode.

I liked the previous version, it so difficult to search through this new version. I just hate it, i may move to alltrails app. On this app i look at specific state , or place, and they show me trails from other states , yeah great .

Not usable, needs work. On a 4 mi snowshoe trip, it indicated 11.4K of elevation climb that was realistically 1.5K ft. Hike duration 0 minutes, huh? Change to terms of service on launch, so approach was...wait til user tries to start recording the hike, then sign you out, don't retain the login, and no screen to agree to TOS anyway. Fortunately I had cell signal.

could not access downloaded maps when out of cell range. I downloaded them before my backpacking trip and kept getting a message stating "no network" when trying to load them. I would expect REI of all companies to understand the need for offline maps to function without network.

Terrible. Won't let you finish a trail if you're in an area near one of their authorized trails, even though there are a ton of trails not on here. And these are real state park trails, not some unauthorized backcountry trail! Incredibly disappointed.

I love this app! I'm getting used to it so I'll update my review in another month or 2. I've been using g all trails for years but it's become harder to navigate, this is straightforward and works great. My go to for hiking for the past 6 weeks, good for backcountry camping too.

Great app.. trails are spot on where other GPS shows old maps. Hopefully someday it will show your tracking, but it does show your position. Nice to have a full state of hikes with a small download. Great for finding new trails.

Post-update, many views are broken (they navigate to a soft locked screen with no buttons to go back) and the back button doesn't work in many views. Previous version was stable, but this update seems to have been rushed.

Mostly good, but my biggest issue is navigating the map. If I press my "Back" button, it will go to the previously-viewed trail rather than just returning to the map. Feels counterintuitive and amounting. Otherwise good

finally a real competitor to alltrails. this has all the data from the REI national parks app, and then all the usgs data for the traila themselves. an entore region can be downloaded right away instead of just individual trails like on alltrails. and best of all -- it's free! thanks REI!

Great app! I love being able to use this out hiking and can visually see where I'm at in a trail using GPS. It's nice to be able to see elevation profiles, distances, photos, and descriptions for the trails.

Not intuitive...couldn't fond anything I cared about. I wanted guidance on how to access trail heads and GPS help with trail itself. Only thing i liked was it gave trail lengths and elevation but I dont need an app for that. I also had troble browsing trails in my area.
This app allows me to plot my hikes and calculate distance and altitude, as well as up to date trail conditions, which is very helpful for safe preparation. I love the feedback from other hikers!!

Great app! Very detailed and I love the way you can see the percentage of the grade you are climbing. It puts things in perspective for me. Also, I like that you can see how far you have hiked. These two items in this app help to plan a day hike or hiking for a week. Thank you.

This app is hard to use. The "favorites" feature isn't very intuitive. Whenever I search for a hike, it brings up results that I'm obviously not interested in. Why show me results for hikes in the UK, when I'm searching in Arizona?

Nice but not overly intuitive and doesn't seem to have a "hikes near me function" including being able to search based on difficulty level. There doesn't appear to be a legend either so you know the difficulty based on symbol

The best hiking trail app I've come across. Great trail discriptions, easy to find and browse trails on map, pinned maps work offline, ad-free, extensive database of trails. Now I want to go shopping at REI to show some financial support for the company that produced this great app!

Download ares blocks entire screen. I didnt want to give it location access, downloaded the state I was in. It would pop up hikes, but the download area pop up would not go away and I couldn't see the hike. I deleted the app!

Great app for trails and traveling. Gems are great info to add to an itinerary. Helps me plan out trips. Navigation ability has helped me out while in a remote canyon with no cell service. Love user photos, elevation charts and most everything!
Content is good. Biggest problem is that the back button does not work on my Pixel 3 running Android 10. Also the recording feature does not seem to show where I actually hiked.

Very good trail app except that all the downloaded maps are stored in internal memory with no option to change it a SD Card. This means all the downloaded and marked places will be lost when I get a new phone.
This free app is incredible. We love to hike and this has helped us find trails and navigate. I'd like to see a record /planning feature and saving the maps to an SD card.

Easy way to see hiking trails wherever you are headed and get a decent idea beforehand if it's a trail right for whatever type hiker you are (novice or experienced). Plus it's a nice way to catalog which trails you've already done.

I use this app every weekend. I like it. However, the search is pretty crude. I have only one state downloaded yet search gives results in all of North America. Needs a filter. Also, I can't seem to just search for just "gems" or 5* trails. Search within a radius would be truly awesome.

Needs a feature to sort trails by distance and difficulty. Needs to be able to go back in trail search without losing place in scroll. When sharing via link in text, link does not load back up in app.
First impressions. Easy to select an area, swipe to go back, or hit the icons on the bottom. Navigation seems straightforward, and looking to add to and enjoy the boring and wildlife gems section.
GPS helped follow trails in italy. Requires switching between google maps to find some things. Segments of trails between key destinations would be nice. All together a really valuable tool.

Broken. Tried to give it another chance but can't. It requires login but I only get an error message. Why do you need to login? If you are hiking there's no way you can login without a connection... but it won't work on WiFi either so that's moot.

overall it is awful compared to other trail apps. has only 6 trails listed, i live within an hour of several state parks, with no way to add. has no options of value like trail record or work even as a partial GPS. don't waste your time on this garbage.

Great app, just figured out the location setting. But now app is crashing on me. Cleared cache and data but intermittently crashing. Hopefully it settles down. Want to track my next hike now that location is working.

I've found the app to be very useful in my hikes in the US national parks. It is especially helpful when there is no cell reception. I have also used it to ensure i am still on a trail and to see how much further I need to go on a trail.

Love using the app. I find that is very intricate to use, but informative. I would like if the roads on the map which up a little bit or so we could see where trailheads match with the roads for planning.
I attempted to record hikes twice with this app and it failed both times. The second attempt had a beautiful map at the end. I thought it saved, but alas the history shows a 0 mile hike.

Excellent App! I love it that it works offline—even while on airplane mode. It made our hike in the middle of nowhere, NM a more enjoyable experience. Thankful for the developers and the contributors. You guys deserve recognition!
Maybe it was a good app but multiple issues with password, resetting passwords, downloading data.... all in all, a lightweight app at best that can't even get the basics right.
NCT in MI has trailheads missing. It also shows campgrounds where there are none. Maps are very slow to load and app crashes alot. Great idea but needs some work.
I've enjoyed having this resource for many of our hikes. It's helpful to have regions downloaded to our devices. Being able to see recent reports on the condition of the trail has also been helpful.

One annoyance is almost every trail in the NYS forest preserve (or the Northeast for that matter) list dogs on leash. Unfortunately (or fortunately, depending on your views) dogs are allowed off leash in 95% of the northeast terrain. Therefore, it's virtually impossible for every trail to list dogs off leash and be accurate. No matter how many trails I correct or tickets I submit this goes unfixed. So 2 stars. Maybe you'll fix it, maybe not. Up to you if you want accuracy.
This app is awesome. I really like the way it provides a through description of trails but in a very simple interphase, which becomes particularly useful when hiking.

I love how straighforward the interface is when browsing the map for hikes. When I know that I want to hike in a certain area, but I haven't decided which trail or route, I come to this app to survey my options.

1. Have settings on Metric but still shows imperial on the physical map. 2. Shows hikes for other countries before my own. Should be able to limit this. Hiking Project arrogance in not replying in over a year, shows they don't care for their customers.
Very accurate. Better than other trail apps we have used. Love that it downloads to be used when you dont have service which is the case in many hiking instances.
great app, works almost flawlessly offline. Discovered the app on the trail when my "offline" app wasn't working and another hiker showed me this app. downloaded the second I got a cell signal.
Best overall hiking app I've used, perfect for finding trails while traveling and has an amazing amount of information available for free.

It has EVERY trail that I could possibly think of. There is a great deal of information about the histoey of each trail along with all the other technical information. It allows others to post about a trail so that you can get first hamd accounts that provide other important information about the trail.

Hi Clancey, thanks for your feedback.  Have you tried uninstalling and reinstalling the app?  Did it stop working when your phone updated to android 9?  If so, Please try:
1. going to Settings (meaning Android, not Hiking Project)
2. find Apps & notifications or App Manager
3. find Hiking Project
4. tap Storage
5. tap Clear Data

Love being able to see my current elevation and progress towards the destination. Will be interested to see how the app improves over the coming years.

It's the only app that provides ACTUAL trails and their difficulty, 
otherwise you're guessing and doing EXTENSIVE research how difficult your 
trip will be. Other apps rely on purely on Google to provide little 
grey-dashes, which are invisible if Google took the pictures when the trail 
was covered in snow, then they slap a few pictures on the hike and calling 
it a day. If you're hiking, planning a hike, planning a backpack trip 
without this app, you're messing up.

replyContent:
Hey Ashley, 
Thanks for reaching out. Hiking Project is a fully crowdsourced resource, which means that we rely on hikers like you to help share the best trails and hikes in an area. If you'd be willing to help us get more BC content added to the site, check out hikingproject.com/mapping for some tips on getting started. Thanks for your help!
